================================================================================

Section 1:
132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST REGULAR SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 12
S.P. 25 In Senate, January 8, 2025
Caucuses
Received by the Secretary of the Senate on January 6, 2025. Referred to the Committee on
Judiciary pursuant to Joint Rule 308.2 and ordered printed.
DAREK M. GRANT
Secretary of the Senate
Presented by Senator BENNETT of Oxford.
Printed on recycled paper
1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 1 MRSA §402, sub-§1-B is enacted to read:
3 1-B. Legislative caucus. "Legislative caucus" means 3 or more Legislators of the
4 same political party meeting for the purpose of conducting legislative business on behalf
5 of the Legislature or a legislative committee.
6 Sec. 2. 1 MRSA §402, sub-§2, ¶A, as enacted by PL 1975, c. 758, is amended to
7 read:
8 A. The Legislature of Maine and its committees and, subcommittees and legislative
9 caucuses;
10 SUMMARY
1111 This bill provides that legislative caucuses are public proceedings under the Freedom
1122 of Access Act. The bill defines "legislative caucus" as 3 or more Legislators of the same
1133 political party meeting for the purpose of conducting legislative business.
Page 1 - 132LR0056(01)
